All additive on `WorkflowConfig`/`createContainer`, never required:

```ts
// 1. Worker identity + leasing (opt-in). createContainer / createWorkflow options:
interface DistributedExecutionOptions {
  workerId?: string;            // default: `${hostname}:${pid}:${randomSuffix}` — stamped on claim
  leaseTtlMs?: number;          // default = 2 × staleHeartbeatThresholdMs; lease auto-renews via existing heartbeat timer
  partitions?: {
    count: number;              // total partition count across the fleet (fixed, like Temporal history shards)
    owned: number[];            // which partition indices THIS scheduler instance claims (e.g. [0,1] of 8)
  };
  wakeSource?: WakeSource;      // optional push adapter; engine subscribes, still polls as backstop
}

// 2. Push-wake adapter the HOST implements (engine never opens a change stream itself):
interface WakeSource {
  // Engine calls this once at start; adapter invokes `onWake(runId?, partitionKey?)`
  // whenever a run becomes runnable (e.g. host bridges a Mongo change stream / Redis pub-sub).
  subscribe(onWake: (hint: { runId?: string; partitionKey?: number }) => void): () => void; // returns unsubscribe
}

// 3. Repository verbs (added to WorkflowRunRepository, routed through claim()/cursor()):
class WorkflowRunRepository {
  // partition-scoped variants of the existing scheduler reads:
  getReadyToResume(now, limit, opts & { partitions?: number[] }): Promise<LeanWorkflowRun[]>;
  cursorStaleRunning(threshold, opts & { partitions?: number[] }): AsyncIterableIterator<LeanWorkflowRun>;
  // lease-aware claim: stamps ownedBy + leaseExpiresAt atomically with the running transition:
  claimWithLease(runId, transition, patch, { workerId, leaseTtlMs, ...opts }): Promise<WorkflowRun|null>;
  renewLease(runId, { workerId, leaseTtlMs }): Promise<boolean>;        // CAS on ownedBy === me
  releaseLease(runId, { workerId }): Promise<boolean>;                   // clear ownedBy on terminal
}
```
No change to `ctx.*` surface — this is infrastructure below the handler. Defaults (`partitions` unset, `wakeSource` unset, `workerId` auto) reproduce v2.3.4 behaviour byte-for-byte.
